<i> Weather-Plus Forecast.</i>

00:07.508 --> 00:09.775
We got more record heat
movin' in.

00:09.777 --> 00:11.877
My guess is it's from Eurasia,

00:11.879 --> 00:13.512
or even, possibly,

00:13.514 --> 00:16.382
the<i> Dark</i> Continent.

00:16.384 --> 00:18.650
That's where Miss Maisie
comes from.

00:18.652 --> 00:20.386
She raised me.

00:20.388 --> 00:21.687
Jesus, Dickie.
(nervous chuckle)

00:21.689 --> 00:23.822
it's -- it's important
to remember

00:23.824 --> 00:25.557
old Dickie comes
from a different era.

00:25.559 --> 00:26.725
Right, Terry?

00:26.727 --> 00:28.627
Oh, that's right.

00:28.629 --> 00:32.464
Sometimes I forget
(tearfully) that he's gone.

00:32.466 --> 00:35.634
As the week-long
beat wave continues --

00:35.636 --> 00:37.136
beat wave?
What's a beat wave?

00:37.138 --> 00:39.705
As the heat wave --
sorry -- continues --

00:39.707 --> 00:42.541
(sobs)

00:42.543 --> 00:44.209
I just hate
seeing Greg like this.

00:44.211 --> 00:46.178
Guy's been a mess
ever since Terry

00:46.180 --> 00:48.580
dumped him and left town
to follow 311 on tour.

00:48.582 --> 00:49.815
You know what?

00:49.817 --> 00:51.350
Greg needs a new man,

00:51.352 --> 00:53.252
and I'm gonna
help him find one.

00:53.254 --> 00:54.553
Why?

00:54.555 --> 00:56.655
Because that's
what you do for friends.

00:56.657 --> 00:58.924
At least, that's what
<i> I</i> do for friends.

00:58.926 --> 01:02.027
In high school, my nickname
was Superfriend.

01:02.029 --> 01:05.364
Actually,
it was Supermouth.

01:05.366 --> 01:06.865
Actually, it was
Suckmachine.

01:06.867 --> 01:09.334
They called me
Stan The Man.

01:09.336 --> 01:12.237
There was a girl
in my class named Stan.

01:12.239 --> 01:15.174
(band plays)

01:15.176 --> 01:18.110
¶ Good morning, U.S.A. ¶

01:18.112 --> 01:21.547
