Aah!

01:39.366 --> 01:42.267
¶ Good morning, U.S.A. ¶

01:42.269 --> 01:45.037
(tranquil tune plays)

01:45.039 --> 01:47.306
Just a little
more pepper.

01:47.308 --> 01:48.907
Greg's coming
up the driveway!

01:48.909 --> 01:51.076
Aah! Aaaaaaah!

01:51.078 --> 01:52.811
Now, remember --

01:52.813 --> 01:54.446
We're pumping him
for information

01:54.448 --> 01:56.148
about his perfect guy

01:56.150 --> 01:58.283
so we can find someone
to set him up with.

01:58.285 --> 02:00.419
It's actually
the perfect temperature.

02:00.421 --> 02:02.554
Can someone toss me a tecate?
-I'll tell you

02:02.556 --> 02:04.823
what my perfect man
would be if I was gay.

02:04.825 --> 02:07.493
He'd have smooth,
soft skin,

02:07.495 --> 02:08.827
long, shiny hair,

02:08.829 --> 02:10.629
a narrow waist
and wide hips,

02:10.631 --> 02:12.598
forming the shape
of an hourglass.

02:12.600 --> 02:14.800
Pouty lips,
big doe eyes.

02:14.802 --> 02:17.302
A musical,
high-pitched voice.

02:17.304 --> 02:20.606
Large, supple, breast-like
pectoral muscles.

02:20.608 --> 02:21.974
And huge balls.

02:21.976 --> 02:23.609
Something you can really
grab onto.

02:23.611 --> 02:24.676
Stan!

02:24.678 --> 02:26.745
Oh, we're
at dinner now.

02:26.747 --> 02:28.280
Thank you so much
for having me.

02:28.282 --> 02:29.748
It's nice to get out
of the house.

02:29.750 --> 02:31.116
Our pleasure.

02:31.118 --> 02:33.785
Now, what would you
like for dessert,

02:33.787 --> 02:37.356
a<i> bear</i> claw
or a<i> twink-ie?</i>

02:37.358 --> 02:40.092
Or maybe
<i> Asian</i> dessert?

02:40.094 --> 02:41.760
We haven't even
eaten dinner yet.

02:41.762 --> 02:43.262
Okay, then,
let's start with salad.

02:43.264 --> 02:44.763
Would you like your
dressing on the<i> top</i>

02:44.765 --> 02:46.932
of your salad,
or on the bottom?

02:46.934 --> 02:48.600
How would you put it
on the bottom?

02:50.337 --> 02:52.638
Okay, what are you two
up to?

02:52.640 --> 02:54.306
All right.
The truth is

02:54.308 --> 02:56.508
we were trying
to figure out your type

02:56.510 --> 02:57.843
so we could set you up.

02:57.845 --> 03:00.279
You just seem so down
ever since Terry left.

03:00.281 --> 03:02.948
Oh.
That's sweet of you.

03:02.950 --> 03:05.384
I admit, I do miss Terry
as a life partner,

03:05.386 --> 03:07.519
but to be honest,
I miss him more right now

03:07.521 --> 03:09.555
as a work partner.

03:09.557 --> 03:10.956
I'm -- I'm sorry.
That -- that probably

03:10.958 --> 03:12.524
didn't exactly warrant
a spit-take.

03:12.526 --> 03:14.293
Kind of jumped the gun
there. Go on.

03:14.295 --> 03:16.962
What makes a reporter,
journalistic integrity?

03:16.964 --> 03:18.664
Ha!
It's the banter!

03:18.666 --> 03:21.033
But you can't just plug anybody
into that other chair.

03:21.035 --> 03:23.702
You need chemistry
and chemistry is hard.

03:23.704 --> 03:25.137
Tell me about it.

03:25.139 --> 03:27.239
I burned down my school
in chemistry class.

03:27.241 --> 03:30.075
My school experience
was pretty<i> flaming,</i> too,

03:30.077 --> 03:32.010
if you know what I mean.
(chuckle)

03:32.012 --> 03:33.712
I bet you were quite
the fire-starter.

03:33.714 --> 03:34.980
Just call me
young Drew Barrymore.

03:34.982 --> 03:36.848
You're not the only one
who liked

03:36.850 --> 03:38.650
"Riding in Cars
with Boys."

03:38.652 --> 03:39.718
"Charlie's Angels"!

03:39.720 --> 03:41.019
"Charlie's Angels 2"!

03:41.021 --> 03:42.187
"Home Fries"!

03:42.189 --> 03:43.355
(gasp) Francine,

03:43.357 --> 03:44.923
do you realize
what we're doing?

03:44.925 --> 03:46.925
We're bantering.
Crazy idea --

03:46.927 --> 03:49.061
Would you come fill in
in Terry's old seat?

03:49.063 --> 03:51.063
Just until we find
a permanent replacement.

03:51.065 --> 03:52.397
I don't know, Greg.

03:52.399 --> 03:54.233
